---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Mariani Family — Customer Story — Formic"
  description="Mariani Family closed labor gaps and reduced ergonomic strain with a flexible Formic deployment."
  ogTitle="Mariani Family — Formic Customer Story"
  ogDescription="Filled staffing gaps, boosted efficiency, swapped equipment as needs evolved."
>
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://formic.co/stories/mariani-family" slot="head" />

<div class="detail-bc">
  <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span><a href="/stories">Customer Stories</a><span class="sep">/</span>Mariani Family
</div>

<section class="detail-hero">
  <div class="si">
    <div class="slabel" style="color:var(--orange)">Customer Story · Mariani Family</div>
    <h1>The line that <em>flexes</em>.</h1>
    <p class="lede">Mariani Family had labor gaps and ergonomic strain limiting efficiency just as demand was rising. One Formic system filled the staffing gap — and got swapped to a different configuration when needs shifted, no renegotiation required.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dark">
  <div class="detail-video wide">
    <div class="detail-video-frame">
      <video autoplay muted loop playsinline poster="/Focus-7603.jpg">
        <source src="/Formic-Header.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
      </video>
      <span class="dv-fpo">FPO</span>
      <span class="dv-cap">Mariani Family · production cell</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">01 — The Challenge</div>
      <h2>Labor gaps, <em>rising demand</em>.</h2>
      <p>Mariani Family was juggling two pressures at once: hiring couldn't keep up with end-of-line demand, and the operators they did have were burning out on repetitive lifts. Demand was climbing — they needed throughput now, not after a six-month CapEx cycle.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Persistent staffing gaps in the highest-friction roles</li>
        <li>Rising ergonomic strain on existing operators</li>
        <li>Demand growing faster than headcount could absorb</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Focus-7603.jpg" alt="Mariani Family floor" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">High-mix production line</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block lgrey">
  <div class="db-grid flip">
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/CasepackerPromoVideo_NoText.gif" alt="Formic system at Mariani Family" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Flexible · swappable</span></div>
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">02 — The Solution</div>
      <h2>One system. <em>Many shapes.</em></h2>
      <p>One Formic deployment, configured to the line's current top-friction task — and re-spec'd later when product mix shifted. The Full Service model meant no second contract, no second integration, no fight over who pays for the change.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Single Formic system filling the highest-friction role</li>
        <li>Equipment swapped under the same Full Service agreement when needs shifted</li>
        <li>No CapEx, no procurement cycle, no renegotiation</li>
        <li>Operators redeployed to higher-judgment work</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dark">
  <div class="si" style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;padding:80px;text-align:center">
    <div class="db-tag" style="justify-content:center">03 — The Outcome</div>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:clamp(40px,5vw,72px);font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.02em;line-height:1;color:var(--white);margin:18px 0 56px">Filled the gap. <em style="color:var(--orange);font-style:normal">Kept flexing.</em></h2>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:1px;background:rgba(255,255,255,.1)">
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:36px 24px"><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:48px;font-weight:500;color:var(--orange);line-height:1">1</div><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(240,245,241,.55);margin-top:12px">System deployed</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:36px 24px"><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:48px;font-weight:500;color:var(--orange);line-height:1">2x</div><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(240,245,241,.55);margin-top:12px">Configurations run</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:36px 24px"><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:48px;font-weight:500;color:var(--orange);line-height:1">$0</div><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(240,245,241,.55);margin-top:12px">Swap CapEx</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-cta">
  <h2>Build a line<br><em>that flexes with you.</em></h2>
  <div class="btn-row">
    <a href="mailto:sales@formic.co" class="btn-ctadark">Get Started</a>
    <a href="/stories" class="btn-ctawh">More Customer Stories</a>
  </div>
</section>
</Layout>
